ORM - object relationship Maping

1.npm install Express create node_modules in folder
2. npm install MongoDB
3. npm install nodemon --save-dev   // will create dev dependency
4. replace 
    "test": "echo \"Error: no test specified\" && exit 1"
    with====> 
"start":"nodemon index.js"
  in package.json in script
5.add 
    "type":"module",
    below licence in package.json so that you can use import insted of require.
6.connect the backend by using MongoClient;
7. use a function and put all mongo code inside that function and then call function while checking it using console.log 
8.  after connecting to the database(mogodb connection) then and then only it should shart your application (order maters)
9.   surround your app in try and catch   
10. CRUD ==> update , delete , create , read.
11.create seperate folder forrout and services.
12.
11.when ever you use  find() querry always use ".toArray("  ==> find().toArray(); sothat the output get in array.



cmd 

1.mkdir to create folder
2.clear - clear the code from cmd
3. cd ===>to get inside a folder
4. show dbs  ==>to show default database
5. mongo ==> to get inside the MongoDB
6. use databasename ==>If you want to use a database with name <mydbdatabasename>, 
   then "use databasename" statement will try to find a database of name databasename
    if it dont find it will create one. 
7.db ==> it will tell which database you are in.
8. beforeinsrting the data verify it like special character and all.
9. while updating convert id into ObjectId  ==> {_id: ObjectId(req.params.id) }
 10. findOneAndUpdate   ===>  by default this will return old record before showing the update 
 so use ==> {ReturnDocument:"after"} it is by default {ReturnDocument:"before"}
